messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 3/25/03 1:12:53 PM Eastern Standard Time, unolist@aol.com ... if you go to
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 3/25/03 1:12:53 PM Eastern Standard Time, unolist@...
writes:

> Where are you?
> >
> >Holly wants to see it live and hasn't.
>

if you go to <A HREF="http://www.broadwayacrossamerica.com/">http://www.broadwayacrossamerica.com/</A>
and select JC Superstar from the dropdown menu, it will show the cities on
the tour. Sebastian Bach is starring in this, which is interesting to this
80's child who remembers him from Skid Row(the band). As I said, my mom got
this for us. She gets season tickets to the broadway series in Columbus every
year and gets opportunities to get tickets early. Funny thing is, I OD'd on
broadway as a child from all the exposure from my mom. I grew up with the
soundtrack from A Chorus Line blaring through the house, cursewords and all
LOL. I went to see one of the last productions in the Shubert Theatre back in
89 or 90 in New York when I was a senior on a high school drama club trip.

Ang
